The course is planned for students-dentists to give the knowledge of normal development of infant and child, and of diseases in childhood.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to prepare young dentists well trained in  normal growth and development from birth up to puberty, physiological differences of organ systems in different periods of childhood, care of infants, their feeding, prevention, diagnostics and therapy of diseases  in childhood.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student will: a) know the child development phases and their age-specific characteristics, b) know the basic principles of growing up and disease prevention, c) know theoretical viewpoints about the peculiarities of childhood in the functioning of organ systems, d) know the basics of infant feeding and care and be able to nurse and feed babies and infants at the elementary level, e) be able to give advice on the treatment of the most common children's diseases, f) be able to communicate with children of different ages, g) be able to take an anamnesis on their own, h) be able to carry out a basic examination of  children and to spot the most important symptoms.
